data: Jean-Francois Van Huele Jean-Francois Van Huele Associate Professor N151 ESC 801.422.4481 vanhuele@byu.edu physics.byu.edu/faculty/vanhuele anytime and by appointment Discussions in Theoretical Physics (Fall 2020) Tue 3:30-4:00 p.m every other week (9/22, etc.) by Zoom https://byu.zoom.us/j/95814523674?pwd=ajhqbWF3Y1FEdUVROXBlSzFHS2pMZz09 Quantum Research Meetings (Fall 2020) Thu 1:00-1:50 p.m. by Zoom https://byu.zoom.us/j/93285596190?pwd=NHY3bStwWm5sd2preVB2RFpFR1dJdz09 Specialty: all aspects of quantum theory, especially quantum dynamics and quantum information I obtained all my physics degrees at the Vrije Universiteit Brussel (VUB) in Belgium. I have taught at Brigham Young University (BYU) since 1988. My research interest centers on all aspects of the quantum.
